race.comment: COAL CRUSHER (3) won this race in 2023 and finished third to Briasa last year. Back to his best this prep and gets the right set-up today. Faded late from the wide gate when fourth in the Russell Balding over 1300m at Randwick. Brings the right form and set to peak. YORKSHIRE (14) untapped gelding with the ability to take this out first-up. Kept smashing the clock last time in and not sure where his ceiling is. Given the two solid trials and backed off the map in early betting. Goes close. ACCREDITED (11) sat on the good tempo as fav when resuming for a narrow second over 1100m at Randwick. Fitter now and drops sharply in weight. Sure to be thereabouts. AIRMAN (5) tough gelding hard fit for this and is going much better than his current price suggests. Respect. OSTRAKA (7) capable on his day and worth thought.
